   1995-12-22T09:05:02 = 1995-12-22, 𐐙𐑉𐐴
  -0010-09-15T04:44:23 = -10-09-15, 𐐝𐐰𐐻

=head3 yMMM (y MMM)

   2008-02-05T18:30:30 = 2008 𐐙𐐯𐐺
   1995-12-22T09:05:02 = 1995 𐐔𐐨𐑅
  -0010-09-15T04:44:23 = -10 𐐝𐐯𐐹

=head3 yMMMEd (y MMM d, E)

   2008-02-05T18:30:30 = 2008 𐐙𐐯𐐺 5, 𐐓𐐭𐑆
   1995-12-22T09:05:02 = 1995 𐐔𐐨𐑅 22, 𐐙𐑉𐐴
  -0010-09-15T04:44:23 = -10 𐐝𐐯𐐹 15, 𐐝𐐰𐐻

=head3 yMMMM (y MMMM)

   2008-02-05T18:30:30 = 2008 𐐙𐐯𐐺𐑉𐐭𐐯𐑉𐐨
   1995-12-22T09:05:02 = 1995 𐐔𐐨𐑅𐐯𐑋𐐺𐐲𐑉
  -0010-09-15T04:44:23 = -10 𐐝𐐯𐐹𐐻𐐯𐑋𐐺𐐲𐑉

=head3 yMMMd (y MMM d)

   2008-02-05T18:30:30 = 2008 𐐙𐐯𐐺 5
   1995-12-22T09:05:02 = 1995 𐐔𐐨𐑅 22
  -0010-09-15T04:44:23 = -10 𐐝𐐯𐐹 15

=head3 yMd (y-MM-dd)

   2008-02-05T18:30:30 = 2008-02-05
   1995-12-22T09:05:02 = 1995-12-22
  -0010-09-15T04:44:23 = -10-09-15

=head3 yQQQ (y QQQ)

   2008-02-05T18:30:30 = 2008 𐐗1
   1995-12-22T09:05:02 = 1995 𐐗4
  -0010-09-15T04:44:23 = -10 𐐗3

=head3 yQQQQ (y QQQQ)

   2008-02-05T18:30:30 = 2008 1𐑅𐐻 𐐿𐐶𐐪𐑉𐐻𐐲𐑉
   1995-12-22T09:05:02 = 1995 4𐑉𐑃 𐐿𐐶𐐪𐑉𐐻𐐲𐑉
  -0010-09-15T04:44:23 = -10 3𐑉𐐼 𐐿𐐶𐐪𐑉𐐻𐐲𐑉

=head3 yw-count-other ('week' w 'of' Y)

   2008-02-05T18:30:30 = week 6 of 2008
   1995-12-22T09:05:02 = week 51 of 1995
  -0010-09-15T04:44:23 = week 37 of -10


=head2 Miscellaneous

=head3 Prefers 24 hour time?

Yes

=head3 Local first day of the week

7 (𐐝𐐲𐑌𐐼𐐩)

=head2 Strftime Patterns

=head3 %c (%a %b %e %H:%M:%S %Y) - date time format

   2008-02-05T18:30:30 = 𐐓𐐭𐑆 𐐙𐐯𐐺  5 18:30:30 2008
   1995-12-22T09:05:02 = 𐐙𐑉𐐴 𐐔𐐨𐑅 22 09:05:02 1995
  -0010-09-15T04:44:23 = 𐐝𐐰𐐻 𐐝𐐯𐐹 15 04:44:23 -10

=head3 %x (%m/%d/%y) - date format

   2008-02-05T18:30:30 = 02/05/08
   1995-12-22T09:05:02 = 12/22/95
  -0010-09-15T04:44:23 = 09/15/10

=head3 %X (%H:%M:%S) - time format

   2008-02-05T18:30:30 = 18:30:30
   1995-12-22T09:05:02 = 09:05:02
  -0010-09-15T04:44:23 = 04:44:23

=head1 SUPPORT

See L<DateTime::Locale>.

=cut
